6: You must kill... Do not forgive...
8:
That demon—the goddess of fate,
who cursed the dragon and the
sword...
16:
And so will I. I'm not like the rest of
you...
19:
Wait... Don't leave me behind.
Please...
23:
What was it again? "It's good to
reflect on your own actions. But
don't let that be an excuse to stand
around and do nothing."
29:
That old geezer really knew how to
put it. I should borrow that line more
often.
38:
Well done. I'm surprised you could
tell.
42:
In the library... Stella found a journal
left behind...
45:
Lilith said it was from a famous
romance novelist and made me
read it... But it wasn't to my tastes.
50:
Oh? Well, since I'm stuck in here, I
don't know what goes on elsewhere.
55: ...You lent me your power, didn't you?
59:
Swinging a blade around really
wasn't for me. Though I'm sure my
lack of skill did you no favors.
61:
But that one move of yours—where
you come crashing down from
above? I do like that one.
64:
You're different from the others.
After all, you're resonating with me.
You don't need to listen to all that
business with the curse.
74:
And you did. You made your wish
and set out to fulfill it. You're
stronger than any Champion I know.
79:
You think so? Then... maybe I've
been wrong this whole time.
84:
If that's how you feel, why not speak
with the one you truly came to see?
87:
Luce. Do me a favor and guide the
boy.
92:
He's pretty shy—won't say a word.
But he'll take you where you need to
go.
95: Just reach out and take his hand.
109:
Don't mention it, friend. You already
did me the biggest favor when you
managed to break that girl out of
her shell, after all!
117:
You... You were one of the voices in
the curse.
120:
But... I guess you must have some
regrets.
125: Thank you. I'll be okay from here.
130: So... You, too, have finally come.
132:
Tell me, boy... Will you join the curse
of the sword?
140:
...I don't think I could, even if I wanted
to. Not like you.
143: Then what brings you to this place?
149:
...I used to hate people who were
weak, I think.
153:
People who were so afraid of being
alone that they'd give up who they
were, just to fit in with the crowd...
157:
People who ran away, because they
couldn't admit to themselves that
they were just as weak...
160:
I hated them. I thought they were
useless.
164:
I've never been a kind person. I want
to be, but... I never was.
168:
...That's why I respected you, in a
way.
173:
Oghir, Lord of Shadow... Please. I
need your help!
175:
I can't carry the weight of the world. I
can't be what everyone needs me to
be. All I can do is keep pushing
forward!
178:
Please, lend me some of your
kindness! A little is all I ask!
182:
Come with me, Oghir! You want to
save her too, don't you?
186:
...You would have me walk the path
of light? After everything?
190:
You would ask me to look to the
light, when these eyes have gleaned
nothing but darkness?
194:
What do you mean? The light is
already here!
244:
Prepare yourself, Nova. Once I've
given you a thrashing...
